"{\"uid\": \"wired.com-story-paris-summer-olympics-2024-purple-track-athletics-mondo\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"THIS STORY ORIGINALLY appeared onWIRED en Espa\\u00f1oland has been translated from Spanish.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 86, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Traditionally, the athleticstrack in an Olympic stadium is red.\", \"from\": 88, \"to\": 151, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, at the 2024 Summer Olympics, it's purple, to match the event colors chosen by the Paris organizing committee.\", \"from\": 152, \"to\": 270, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 243, \"end\": 248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999780770852, \"rank\": 2.1922853307660356e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But there is another difference: It's made with recycled shells produced by the fishing industry, as part of the 2024 Olympics' commitment to sustainability.\", \"from\": 271, \"to\": 428, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Resilient flooring, such as running-track flooring, is made using calcium carbonate, which is usually obtained through mining.\", \"from\": 430, \"to\": 556, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, the company that designed the track for the 2024 Summer Olympics, Mondo, teamed up with a fisher's cooperative to gather shells of bivalve mollusks from the Mediterranean Sea, such as mussels and clams, which are rich in the material.\", \"from\": 557, \"to\": 800, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 632, \"end\": 637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_Media\", \"score\": 0.7405554249299091, \"rank\": 0.3108828573954707, \"text\": \"Mondo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_Media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_Media\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The shells would have otherwise gone to waste.\", \"from\": 801, \"to\": 847, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The track is functionally the same as a traditional one, with the aim being to consolidate the creation of a new, resilient, sustainable sports flooring.\", \"from\": 849, \"to\": 1002, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mondo teamed up withNieddittas, an Italian fishing cooperative specializing in mollusks, to get the materials it needed.\", \"from\": 1004, \"to\": 1124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1004, \"end\": 1009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_Media\", \"score\": 0.7405554249299091, \"rank\": 0.3108828573954707, \"text\": \"Mondo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_Media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_Media\"}, {\"begin\": 1039, \"end\": 1046, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.8612176669698931, \"rank\": 0.1592917038892266, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Its fishers cleaned and dried waste shells from harvested mussels and clams, grounded them into a fine powder, and sent the material to the flooring manufacturer to make the track.\", \"from\": 1125, \"to\": 1305, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The scientists in charge of the project worked on perfecting the technique for three years.\", \"from\": 1306, \"to\": 1397, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The sports industry can reduce its ecological impact by using seashells this way.\", \"from\": 1399, \"to\": 1480, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mining of limestone and marble to gather calcium carbonate produces carbon emissions, as well as mining waste.\", \"from\": 1481, \"to\": 1591, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According to Mondo, the construction of a track using biogenic calcium carbonate offsets the emissions of a Euro 4 diesel vehicle driving 60,000 kilometers.\", \"from\": 1592, \"to\": 1748, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1605, \"end\": 1610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_Media\", \"score\": 0.7405554249299091, \"rank\": 0.3108828573954707, \"text\": \"Mondo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_Media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_Media\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The project serves as a forward-looking example of a long-term commitment to sustainability and local communities,\\\"Nieddittassaid in a press release.\", \"from\": 1749, \"to\": 1899, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The new athletics track measures 17,000 square meters, cost approximately \\u20ac3 million, and has a lifespan of 10 years.\", \"from\": 1901, \"to\": 2018, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mondo has now designed tracks for 12 editions of theOlympic Gamesin total, including the red one for Tokyo 2020.\", \"from\": 2019, \"to\": 2131, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2019, \"end\": 2024, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_Media\", \"score\": 0.7405554249299091, \"rank\": 0.3108828573954707, \"text\": \"Mondo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_Media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_Media\"}, {\"begin\": 2120, \"end\": 2125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9983184118328029, \"rank\": 0.0013232857359834005, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With each Olympics, the technology of the track material improves.\", \"from\": 2132, \"to\": 2198, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Tokyo, the top of the track was composed of 3D rubber granules that worked together with a system of polymers placed on the top layer.\", \"from\": 2200, \"to\": 2337, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2203, \"end\": 2208, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9983184118328029, \"rank\": 0.0013232857359834005, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2247, \"end\": 2249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/3D_computer_graphics\", \"score\": 0.8067803632266275, \"rank\": 0.11050425036499784, \"text\": \"3D\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/3D_computer_graphics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/3D_computer_graphics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With this, athletes were expected to achieve greater speed-and indeed, this was the stage on which the Jamaican track and field athlete Elaine Thompson-Herah won gold in the women's 100-meter race with a time of 10.61 seconds, becoming the second-fastest woman in history.\", \"from\": 2338, \"to\": 2610, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2441, \"end\": 2449, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9999996331888032, \"rank\": 3.667987301962252e-07, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}, {\"begin\": 2474, \"end\": 2495, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elaine_Thompson-Herah\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elaine Thompson-Herah\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elaine_Thompson-Herah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elaine_Thompson-Herah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In total, eight Olympic track records were broken at the 2020 games.\", \"from\": 2611, \"to\": 2679, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mondo says it has since further perfected the technology, meaning the Paris track could see even more records fall.\", \"from\": 2681, \"to\": 2796, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2681, \"end\": 2686, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_Media\", \"score\": 0.7405554249299091, \"rank\": 0.3108828573954707, \"text\": \"Mondo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_Media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_Media\"}, {\"begin\": 2751, \"end\": 2756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999780770852, \"rank\": 2.1922853307660356e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But to find out just how fast it is, you will have to tune in to the track events, which begin on August 1.\", \"from\": 2797, \"to\": 2904, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"More From WIRED  Reviews and Guides  \\u00a92026Cond\\u00e9 Nast.\", \"from\": 2906, \"to\": 2959, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All rights reserved.WIREDmay earn a portion of sales from products that are purchased through our site as part of our Affiliate Partnerships with retailers.\", \"from\": 2960, \"to\": 3116, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The material on this site may not be reproduced, distributed, transmitted, cached or otherwise used, except with the prior written permission of Cond\\u00e9 Nast.Ad Choices\", \"from\": 3117, \"to\": 3283, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3262, \"end\": 3267, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis,_Grand_Cond\\u00e9\", \"score\": 0.7069136048507194, \"rank\": 0.19609582963621316, \"text\": \"Cond\\u00e9\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis,_Grand_Cond\\u00e9\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis,_Grand_Cond\\u00e9\"}]}]}"